Verify:* Header contains \"Bearer {token}\"\n80:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::test_auth_header_set`\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T013** Test No Authorization header when token is empty\n83:   - *File:* `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n84:   - *Verify:* Authorization header not in request\n85:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::test_no_auth_header`\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T014** Test x-agentcube-session-id header in CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n88:   - *File:* `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n89:   - *Verify:* Header present in requests\n90:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py::test_session_header`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T015** Test x-agentcube-session-id header in AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n93:   - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n94:   - *Verify:* Header present in requests\n95:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::test_session_header`\n96: \n97: - [ ] **T016** Test timeout tuple construction\n98:   - *File:* `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n99:   - *Verify:* timeout=(connect_timeout, self.timeout)\n100:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py::test_timeout_tuple`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T017** Test per-call timeout override (timeout + 2.0)\n103:   - *File:* `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n104:   - *Verify:* execute_command(timeout=60) uses 62s read timeout\n105:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py::test_per_call_timeout`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Phase 4: Unit Tests - URL & Body (T018-T022)\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T018** Test ControlPlaneClient base_url from env var\n112:   - *File:* `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n113:   - *Verify:* WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var used\n114:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::test_base_url_from_env`\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T019** Test ControlPlaneClient base_url from argument\n117:   - *File:* `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n118:   - *Verify:* Argument takes precedence over env var\n119:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::test_base_url_from_arg`\n120: \n121: - [ ] **T020** Test CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient URL construction\n122:   - *File:* `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n123:   - *Verify:* URL format: `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr}/invocations/`\n124:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py::test_url_construction`\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T021** Test execute_command request body format\n127:   - *File:* `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n128:   - *Verify:* `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"60s\"}`\n129:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py::test_execute_command_body`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T022** Test write_file base64 encoding\n132:   - *File:* `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n133:   - *Verify:* Content is base64 encoded in body\n134:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py::test_write_file_encoding`\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ### Phase 5: Unit Tests - Token & Logging (T023-T027)\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T023** Test read_token_from_file with existing file\n141:   - *File:* `tests/test_utils.py`\n142:   - *Verify:* Returns token string (stripped)\n143:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_utils.py::test_read_token_from_file_exists`\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T024** Test read_token_from_file with missing file\n146:   - *File:* `tests/test_utils.py`\n147:   - *Verify:* Returns None, no exception\n148:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_utils.py::test_read_token_from_file_missing`\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T025** Test get_logger default level (INFO)\n151:   - *File:* `tests/test_log.py`\n152:   - *Verify:* Logger level is INFO\n153:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_log.py::test_logger_default_level`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T026** Test get_logger with verbose=True (DEBUG)\n156:   - *File:* `tests/test_log.py`\n157:   - *Verify:* Logger level is DEBUG\n158:   - *Test:* `pytest tests/test_log.py::test_logger_verbose`\n15