{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871004848,"sessionID":"ses_285d73342ffeXZgt3El14Z0UyV","part":{"id":"prt_d7a290c47001mmmyaQkism6Pyi","messageID":"msg_d7a28ff780019BUh9ic1vL9ncB","sessionID":"ses_285d73342ffeXZgt3El14Z0UyV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b4081f3332e24aa0816e5d04","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the HTTP underlying client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK (AR-029). It focuses on session management, connection pooling, timeout handling, header management, and error handling for both control plane and data plane communications.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-029\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The AgentCube Python SDK uses HTTP for communication with both the Workload Manager (control plane) and the Router (data plane). This AR defines the HTTP client layer that handles:\n20: - Session management with connection pooling\n21: - Timeout configuration (connect and read timeouts)\n22: - Header management (Authorization, session IDs, Content-Type)\n23: - Request/response handling for different operation types\n24: - Error handling and exception conversion\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Requirements\n29: \n30: ### AR-029-001: HTTP Session 生命周期管理\n31: \n32: The system SHALL manage `requests.Session` lifecycle to ensure proper connection pooling and cleanup.\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: AR-029-001-A — Session creation with connection pooling\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` is called\n37: - **WHEN** the function executes\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n39: - **AND** the adapter SHALL have `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: AR-029-001-B — Session context manager cleanup\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` or `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n44: - **WHEN** the `with` block exits normally\n45: - **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed via `.close()`\n46: - **AND** all HTTP connections SHALL be released back to the pool\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-029-001-C — Session cleanup on exception\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs within a context manager block\n51: - **WHEN** the `__exit__` method is called with exception info\n52: - **THEN** the session SHALL still be closed\n53: - **AND** the original exception SHALL be re-raised after cleanup\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### AR-029-002: HTTP 请求超时行为\n58: \n59: The system SHALL handle connect timeouts and read timeouts correctly for all HTTP operations.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-A — Connect timeout applies to all requests\n62: \n63: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with `connect_timeout=5.0`\n64: - **WHEN** a request is made to an unreachable host\n65: - **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectTimeout` SHALL be raised within 5 seconds\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-B — Read timeout for long-running operations\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a command that takes longer than the read timeout\n70: - **WHEN** the server does not respond within `(connect_timeout + timeout)` seconds\n71: - **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout` SHALL be raised\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-C — Timeout tuple construction\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke` is called with default timeout settings\n76: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n77: - **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be a tuple `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `connect_timeout` defaults to `5.0` and `timeout` defaults to `120`\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-D — Per-call timeout override\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=300)` is called\n82: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n83: - **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `timeout + 2.0` seconds (302 seconds total) to allow for server-side timeout handling\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-E — Default timeout values\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n88: - **WHEN** the client is created\n89: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### AR-029-003: HTTP 头部管理\n94: \n95: The system SHALL correctly set and manage HTTP headers for both control plane and data plane requests.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: AR-029-003-A — Authorization header on control plane\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with a valid `auth_token`\n100: - **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n101: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `Authorization: Bearer {auth_token}`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: AR-029-003-B — No Authorization header when token is empty\n104: \n105: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n106: - **WHEN** a request is made\n107: - **THEN** the `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be included\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: AR-029-003-C — Session ID header for Code Interpreter\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"test-session-123\"`\n112: - **WHEN** `execute_command` is called\n113: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session-123`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: AR-029-003-D — Session ID header for Agent Runtime\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used\n118: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n119: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header defined by `SESSION_HEADER` constant (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: AR-029-003-E — Content-Type header for JSON requests\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** `_request` is called with a JSON body\n124: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n125: - **THEN** the header `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: AR-029-003-F — Multipart upload content-type\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** `upload_file` is called\n130: - **WHEN** the request is sent as multipart/form-data\n131: - **THEN** the outer request SHALL NOT have `Content-Type: application/json`\n132: - **AND** the `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL still be included\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ### AR-029-004: HTTP 错误处理\n137: \n138: The system SHALL handle HTTP error responses appropriately and convert them to SDK-specific exceptions.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: AR-029-004-A — Non-200 response on create session\n141: \n142: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` receives HTTP 400 or 500\n143: - **WHEN** the response is not successful\n144: - **THEN** an appropriate `requests.exceptions.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: AR-029-004-B — 404 treated as success for delete\n147: \n148: - **GIVEN** `delete_session` is called with a non-existent `session_id`\n149: - **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404\n150: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (treating \"not found\" as successful deletion)\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: AR-029-004-C — Connection error handling\n153: \n154: - **GIVEN** the Router is unreachable\n155: - **WHEN** a data plane request is made\n156: - **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectionError` SHALL be raised\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: AR-029-004-D — Response JSON parsing failure\n159: \n160: - **GIVEN** the server returns non-JSON response\n161: - **WHEN** `execute_command` tries to parse the response as JSON\n162: - **THEN** a `JSONDecodeError` or equivalent SHALL be raised\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ### AR-029-005: Base URL 解析与构造\n167: \n168: The system SHALL correctly resolve and construct base URLs for both control plane and data plane.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: AR-029-005-A — Control plane URL from environment\n171: \n172: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable is set to `https://wm.example.com`\n173: - **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without arguments\n174: - **WHEN** the client is used\n175: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `https://wm.example.com`\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: AR-029-005-B — Control plane URL from argument\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"https://custom-wm.example.com\")`\n180: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n181: - **THEN** argument SHALL take precedence over environment variable\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-029-005-C — Data plane base URL from router\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n186: - **AND** `base_url` is NOT provided\n187: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n188: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: AR-029-005-D — Data plane base URL explicit override\n191: \n192: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with explicit `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"`\n193: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n194: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be exactly `https://custom.example.com/api`\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: AR-029-005-E — Agent Runtime base URL construction\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n199: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n200: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ### AR-029-006: 请求体构造\n205: \n206: The system SHALL construct HTTP request bodies correctly for different operation types.\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: AR-029-006-A — Execute command JSON body\n209: \n210: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]` and `timeout=60`\n211: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n212: - **THEN** the JSON body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"60s\"}`\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: AR-029-006-B — Write file base64 encoding\n215: \n216: - **GIVEN** `write_file` is called with `content=\"Hello World\"` and `remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\"`\n217: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n218: - **THEN** the JSON body SHALL include `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: AR-029-006-C — Download file streaming\n221: \n222: - **GIVEN** `download_file` is called\n223: - **WHEN** the GET request is made to `api/files/{clean_path}`\n224: - **THEN** `stream=True` SHALL be set on the request\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: AR-029-006-D — List files query parameter\n227: \n228: - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/tmp\")` is called\n229: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n230: - **THEN** the request SHALL be GET to `api/files` with query parameter `path=/tmp`\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ### AR-029-007: Token 文件读取\n235: \n236: The system SHALL handle token file reading gracefully with appropriate fallback behavior.\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: AR-029-007-A — Token file exists and readable\n239: \n240: - **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `eyJ...`\n241: - **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n242: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n243: - **THEN** `self.token` SHALL be the file contents (stripped)\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: AR-029-007-B — Token file does not exist\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** the service account token file does not exist\n248: - **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n249: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file` is called\n250: - **THEN** it SHALL return an empty string `\"\"`\n251: - **AND** no exception SHALL be raised\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ### AR-029-008: 日志记录\n256: \n257: The system SHALL log HTTP operations for debugging and monitoring purposes.\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: AR-029-008-A — Logger creation with default level\n260: \n261: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube\")` is called\n262: - **WHEN** the logger is created\n263: - **THEN** the default log level SHALL be `logging.INFO`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: AR-029-008-B — Custom logger level\n266: \n267: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n268: - **WHEN** the logger is configured\n269: - **THEN** the logger level SHALL be `logging.DEBUG`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: AR-029-008-C — Verbose mode enables debug logging\n272: \n273: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n274: - **WHEN** the client is created\n275: - **THEN** the logger SHALL be set to `DEBUG` level\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ### AR-029-009: 客户端字段初始化\n280: \n281: The system SHALL correctly initialize all client fields as documented.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: AR-029-009-A — CodeInterpreterClient fields\n284: \n285: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=1800, verbose=True, session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n286: - **WHEN** the client is initialized\n287: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have fields: `name=\"test\"`, `namespace=\"ns\"`, `ttl=1800`, `verbose=True`, `session_id=\"sess-1\"`, `cp_client`, `dp_client`, `router_url`, `logger`\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: AR-029-009-B — AgentRuntimeClient fields\n290: \n291: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent1\", namespace=\"default\", timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)`\n292: - **WHEN** the client is initialized\n293: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have fields: `agent_name=\"agent1\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `timeout=60`, `connect_timeout=3.0`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`, `logger`\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: AR-029-009-C — ControlPlaneClient defaults\n296: \n297: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized with no arguments\n298: - **WHEN** the client is created\n299: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120`, `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`, `self.pool_connections` SHALL be `10`, `self.pool_maxsize` SHALL be `10`\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ### AR-029-010: 异常类层次结构\n304: \n305: The system SHALL provide a clear exception hierarchy for different error conditions.\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: AR-029-010-A — AgentCubeError is base class\n308: \n309: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeError` is the base exception\n310: - **WHEN** any SDK-specific exception is raised\n311: - **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError`\n312: \n313: #### Scenario: AR-029-010-B — CommandExecutionError attributes\n314: \n315: - **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError` is raised for a failed command\n316: - **WHEN** the exception is caught\n317: - **THEN** it SHALL have `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n318: - **AND** the exception message SHALL include the exit code and stderr\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: AR-029-010-C — SessionError definition exists\n321: \n322: - **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n323: - **WHEN** the module is imported\n324: - **THEN** `SessionError` SHALL be available as `AgentCubeError` subclass\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: AR-029-010-D — DataPlaneError definition exists\n327: \n328: - **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n329: - **WHEN** the module is imported\n330: - **THEN** `DataPlaneError` SHALL be available as `AgentCubeError` subclass\n331: \n332: ---\n333: \n334: ## Non-Requirements\n335: \n336: The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n337: \n338: - Authentication logic beyond token file reading and Bearer token header setting\n339: - TLS/SSL certificate validation configuration (use requests defaults)\n340: - Retry logic for transient failures\n341: - Request/response logging at HTTP wire level\n342: - Custom HTTP adapter implementations beyond connection pooling\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: ## Dependencies\n347: \n348: | Dependency | Description |\n349: |------------|-------------|\n350: | AR-028 | AgentRuntimeClient implementation |\n351: | python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n352: | python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification |\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ## Acceptance Criteria\n357: \n358: | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n359: |----|-----------|---------------------|\n360: | AC001 | `create_session` returns Session with HTTPAdapter for http/https | Unit test verifying adapter mount |\n361: | AC002 | Context manager closes session on exit | Integration test with mock server |\n362: | AC003 | Connect timeout raises ConnectTimeout | Test against unreachable host |\n363: | AC029-004 | Read timeout raises ReadTimeout | Test with slow server response |\n364: | AC005 | Authorization header set when token provided | Mock server assertion |\n365: | AC006 | Session ID header sent on data plane requests | Request inspection test |\n366: | AC007 | 404 on delete returns True | Unit test with mock response |\n367: | AC008 | Base URL constructed correctly from router | Path construction verification |\n368: | AC009 | Request body format matches specification | JSON structure validation |\n369: | AC010 | Token file fallback returns empty string | Test with missing file |\n370: | AC011 | Logger respects verbose flag | Level inspection test |\n371: | AC012 | Exception hierarchy correct | Import and inheritance test |\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Test Strategy\n376: \n377: ### Unit Tests\n378: - Test `create_session` returns properly configured Session\n379: - Test timeout tuple construction\n380: - Test header construction for different request types\n381: - Test URL construction for control plane and data plane\n382: - Test token file reading (with and without file)\n383: - Test exception class hierarchy\n384: \n385: ### Integration Tests\n386: - Test context manager cleanup\n387: - Test actual HTTP requests with mock server\n388: - Test timeout behavior with slow responses\n389: - Test error handling for various HTTP status codes\n390: \n391: ### Mock Server Tests\n392: - Use `responses` or `requests-mock` to simulate HTTP responses\n393: - Verify request headers, bodies, and path construction\n394: - Test edge cases like 404 on delete\n395: \n396: ---\n397: \n398: ## Implementation Notes\n399: \n400: ### Key Components\n401: \n402: | Component | Path | Description |\n403: |-----------|------|-------------|\n404: | `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Creates requests.Session with HTTPAdapter |\n405: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | HTTP client for Workload Manager |\n406: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Code Interpreter Router |\n407: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Agent Runtime Router |\n408: | `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Reads service account token |\n409: | `get_logger` | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Creates configured logger |\n410: | Exception classes | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n411: \n412: ### Configuration Defaults\n413: \n414: | Parameter | Default | Applied To |\n415: |-----------|---------|------------|\n416: | timeout | 120 | All HTTP clients |\n417: | connect_timeout | 5.0 | All HTTP clients |\n418: | pool_connections | 10 | Session adapter |\n419: | pool_maxsize | 10 | Session adapter |\n420: \n421: ### Header Constants\n422: \n423: | Header | Value | Usage |\n424: |--------|-------|-------|\n425: | Session ID | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Code Interpreter & Agent Runtime |\n426: | Authorization | `Bearer {token}` | Control plane (when token provided) |\n427: | Content-Type | `application/json` | JSON request bodies |\n\n(End of file - total 427 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the HTTP underlying client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK (AR-029). It focuses on session management, connection pooling, timeout handling, header management, and error handling for both control plane and data plane communications.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-029\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK uses HTTP for communication with both the Workload Manager (control plane) and the Router (data plane). This AR defines the HTTP client layer that handles:\n- Session management with connection pooling","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871004823,"end":1775871004843}}}}
